column102: RequirementText
Error Messages should have a unique number and descriptions of errors should be documented.
Fields on the screens shall be defined as mandatory or optional. Mandatory fields shall require input to complete a transaction.
For specified call types, the system should provide the ability to automatically increase the priority of a call if the call is not closed after a given period of time.

In order to close a help desk call, the system shall provide the ability to send an email notification to the user to request confirmation of the resolution/workaround. The system shall provide a template for this email.

In order to create an Incident Report, the system should provide the ability to add additional detail to the help desk call regarding the actions taken, any previous occurrences of the incident, and the suspected cause of the incident.
It shall be possible to create, edit, delete, lock, and unlock users centrally.
The 1st Level Support user shall have the ability to manually assign a call to a 2nd Level Support user or to another Service desk (if the call was originally assigned to the wrong desk).
The access rights shall be differentiated for the following functionality: Read, Write, Reopen and Close
The Support user assigned to the call shall have the ability to update the call to indicate that their work is complete and to record activities performed/enter comments related to the call.
The Support user shall have the ability to add articles to the Knowledge Base, such as Frequently Asked Questions, Known Errors, and Workarounds.
The Support user shall have the ability to classify the type of call by: Service, Call Type and Category
The Support user(s) shall have the ability to record the amount of time spent on resolving a help desk call.
The system and all related documentation shall be in English.
The system may provide a browser-based web administrator and Support user interface.
The system may provide a graphical display of the relationships between CIs.
The system may provide an out-of-the-box report on the metrics related to the usage of the Knowledge Base by users and by Support users.
The system may provide the ability to assign a help desk call to a 3rd Level Support user and for the 3rd Level Support user to have the ability to update the help desk call.
The system may provide the ability to assign a unique URL to each help desk call.
The system may provide the ability to automatically raise a help desk call in the event of a fault detected on the network.
The system may provide the ability to have multiple views to be open simultaneously on the screen.
The system may provide the ability to integrate with HP OpenView to automatically create help desk calls from errors detected on the network.
The system may provide the ability to integrate with software development configuration management tools for the initial load of software CIs and for updating CI baselines.
The system may provide the ability to launch another application (i.e. by pressing a button or another trigger).
The system may provide the ability to manage software licenses.
The system shall assign a unique identifier to each help desk call.
The system shall assign a unique identifier to each problem record.
The system shall be able to handle 27 active Support users simultaneously on adequate hardware. (7 1st level Support users and 20 2nd level Support users)
The system shall be executable on Sun Solaris version 8 or higher, on Microsoft Windows Server 2003 or higher, or on Linux Servers.
The system shall be scalable for use by more then 500 end users.
The system shall have the ability to launch Novell ZENworks for remote control functionality.
The system shall provide a browser-based web user interface for users.
The system shall provide a Knowledge Base for users and Support users to use to search for Frequently Asked Questions, Known Errors and workarounds.
The system shall provide a reporting tool to allow Support users to develop custom reports using a dynamic set of parameters to sort and filter the data.
The system shall provide a template for adding information to the Knowledge Base.
The system shall provide a user-friendly graphical interface that is easily navigated using drop-down menus and drill-down capabilities.
The system shall provide an out-of-the-box report on the number and type of calls closed by the 1st Level Support and by the 2nd Level Support over a specified period of time.
The system shall provide out-of-the box reports that facilitate the audit of configuration baselines.
The system shall provide out-of-the-box reports on help desk calls filtered by category, department, user, service, priority, or other attributes over a specified period of time.
The system shall provide out-of-the-box reports on help desk calls, problems, known errors, and RFCs associated with a specified CI.
The system shall provide out-of-the-box reports on problem records filtered by category, service, status, time open, priority, or other attributes over s specified period of time.
The system shall provide out-of-the-box reports on RFCs filtered by type, priority, category, impact, related CIs, or other attributes over a specified period of time.

The system shall provide out-of-the-box reports on the metrics related to the amount of time to close a help desk call for each call type and call priority and the percentage of calls closed within the specified deadline.
The system shall provide search and browse functionality for searching for information in the Knowledge Base.
The system shall provide Spell-Check functionality for communications to users.
The system shall provide standard reports on the details of individual help desk calls, problems, RFCs, and CIs.
The system shall provide the ability for a user to reopen a help desk call that he/she raised. The user should have the ability to enter a reason for reopening the call.
The system shall provide the ability for a user to update a help desk call he/she submitted, in response to a request for more information.
The system shall provide the ability for a Support user to create and send an email related to a help desk call, problem, CI, or RFC.

The system shall provide the ability for a Support user to designate how they want to be notified when a help desk call, problem, or RFC is assigned to them. A Support user shall have the ability to specify if they want a pop-up message, an email notification, or no notification at all.
The system shall provide the ability for a Support user to forward a help desk call, a problem, or a RFC as an email.

The system shall provide the ability for a Support user to save user-defined queries or views and to set default sort and filter criteria for viewing the list of help desk calls, problems, CIs, or RFCs.
The system shall provide the ability for a Support users to request more information from a user in relation to a help desk call.
The system shall provide the ability for authorised users to update RFCs throughout the RFC lifecycle.
The system shall provide the ability for end user or Support users to attach documents to help desk calls.
The system shall provide the ability for users and Support users to submit help desk calls and to designate if the call is an IT or GES help desk call.
The system shall provide the ability for the user or Support user to enter free format text to describe the help desk call.
The system shall provide the ability for the user to monitor the status of a call he/she submitted.
The system shall provide the ability to define which fields are visible to the user.
The system shall provide the ability for the Problem Support user assigned to the problem to update the problem with details regarding the activities performed and/or comments related to the problem.
The system shall provide the ability for the Support user to assign a priority and a target closure date to a call.
The system shall provide the ability for the Support user to monitor the status of help desk calls, problems, CIs, and RFCs.
The system shall provide the ability to add configurable CI attributes.
The system shall provide the ability to add configurable CI categories.
The system shall provide the ability to add customisable fields.
The system shall provide the ability to assign a priority and a category to a RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to assign a problem record to a Problem Support user.
The system shall provide the ability to assign a Support user to a RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to assign a unique ID to a RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to assign a unique ID to each CI. The unique ID for the CI shall take into account the CI model, type, or other attributes.
The system shall provide the ability to assign user rights to a module, a table, or a field.
The system shall provide the ability to associate a Knowledge Base article with a help desk call.
The system shall provide the ability to associate affected CIs with a help desk call.
The system shall provide the ability to associate Knowledge Base articles with CIs.
The system shall provide the ability to associate problem records with one or more help desk calls (incidents).
The system shall provide the ability to attach a document to a problem record.
The system shall provide the ability to attach a document to a RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to automatically route a help desk call to the appropriate service desk based on the service and the help desk designated by the user.
The system shall provide the ability to backup and restore all system files and user data, including the database, using Veritas NetBackup Enterprise Server 5.x and higher.
The system shall provide the ability to classify problem records by priority and category.

The system shall provide the ability to close a help desk call directly (without requesting confirmation from the user). The system shall provide the ability to send an automatic email notification to the user notifying the user that the call has been closed. The system shall provide a template for this email.
The system shall provide the ability to create and edit user profiles and assign users to profiles using a GUI.
The system shall provide the ability to create and update a product tree with CIs and to track the relationships between the CIs in the product tree.
The system shall provide the ability to create and use email templates for Support users to send standard communications to users.
The system shall provide the ability to create problem records and to separate them from help desk calls.

The system shall provide the ability to create templates for standard service request help desk calls (e.g. for toner replacements, CD burning requests etc.). The templates shall require the user to enter the necessary details related to the request.
The system shall provide the ability to define business rules to automatically update the details of a CI when a related help desk call, problem, or RFC realises a change in status.
The system shall provide the ability to define the service types and call types for help desk calls to reflect the services and call types managed by the IT Service Desk and the Service Desk.
The system shall provide the ability to direct the output of a report to screen, printer, file or email
The system shall provide the ability to distinguish service requests and change requests and the handling of these two types of requests.
The system shall provide the ability to export any report to plain text, CSV, MS Word, MS Excel, PDF and HTML formats.
The system shall provide the ability to filter and sort help desk calls, problems, CIs, and RFCs by any user defined criteria.
The system shall provide the ability to flag a Knowledge Base article to make it visible to users.
The system shall provide the ability to import asset data from mySAP ERP to create/update configuration items and to export configuration item data to mySAP ERP.
The system shall provide the ability to integrate with Novell GroupWise for sending and receiving emails.
The system shall provide the ability to interface with other databases or directories containing user contact and location details, such as Novell eDirectory and the Oracle Database for the intranet.
The system shall provide the ability to organise Knowledge Base articles in a hierarchy (e.g. by service type) and to create links between related articles.
The system shall provide the ability to perform a validation and consistency check of data upon submission of data for saving.
The system shall provide the ability to print any report in a formatted document.
The system shall provide the ability to record baselines of CIs and CI packages and to record a unique identifier for each baseline.
The system shall provide the ability to record post implementation assessment and review information for a RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to restrict which Support users are able to close a call (e.g. only 1st Level Support users can close a call).
The system shall provide the ability to specify a default time period to allow a user to reopen a call. After the specified time period, the system should not allow the user to reopen the call.
The system shall provide the ability to track all CIs affected by a RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to track all CIs that are scheduled to be upgraded, replaced or decommissioned.
The system shall provide the ability to track all of the ITIL recommended CI attributes.
The system shall provide the ability to track all the information recommended by ITIL in the RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to track and report on the history of changes to a help desk call.
The system shall provide the ability to track CIs affected by an authorised or scheduled Change.
The system shall provide the ability to track component CIs and their version #s in the test and live environments.
The system shall provide the ability to track how a help desk call was submitted (ie via phone, email, or online through the system).
The system shall provide the ability to track known errors as Knowledgebase articles.
The system shall provide the ability to track the back-out plan associated with an RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to track the CAB minutes for an RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to track the CIs affected by a problem.
The system shall provide the ability to track the users contact details and department without requiring the user or 1st Level Support user to enter these details.
The system shall provide the ability to track the help desk calls, problems, RFCs, known errors and Knowledgebase articles that are related to a CI.
The system shall provide the ability to track the history of changes to a CI.
The system shall provide the ability to track the history of changes to a problem record.
The system shall provide the ability to track the history of changes to a RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to track the physical and logical CIs in the CMDB:
The system shall provide the ability to track the related help desk calls, problems, and/or known errors with a RFC.
The system shall provide the ability to track the release contents, including component CIs and their version numbers.
The system shall provide the ability to track the requestor of the change and the users impacted by the change.
The system shall provide the ability to track the solution or work-around for a problem.
The system shall provide the ability to track the status of a CI throughout its lifecycle.
The system shall provide the ability to track the status of a help desk call.
The system shall provide the ability to track the status of a problem record.
The system shall provide the ability to track the status of an RFC throughout its lifecycle.
The system shall provide the ability to track the total amount of time that a RFC was open.
The system shall provide the ability to track the total amount of time that the call was open.
The system shall provide the ability to track the type of resolution/workaround for a help desk call.
The system shall provide the option for the user to search the Knowledge Base prior to raising a help desk call.
The system shall run on Microsoft Windows XP SP 2 and higher versions.
The system shall support drill-down functionality in reports.
The system shall support Microsoft SQL Server or Oracle as the database platform.

The system shall support printing from the client using the standard interface provided by the Microsoft Windows operating system to the standard printers that are configured and installed on the client.
The system shall support single sign-on user authentication for the web-based client with Novel eDirectory or LDAP.
The system shall support SMTP protocol for mail integration.
The system shall support SNMP (Simple Network Management Protocol).
The system shall support TCP/IP as the network protocol.
The system shall support unattended installation of its client via Novell ZENworks.
The system shall support XML Standard for interfaces and data exchange.
The system shall track all activities performed on a help desk call.
The system shall track all communication related to a help desk call, problem, CI, or RFC.
The system should logically group transactions and make transactions available via tool tips, pop-up menus and menu-bars.
The system should provide a process or workflow feature to automate the change management process.
The system should provide the ability for an user to cc another user onto a help desk call.
The system should provide the ability for a Support user to accept (or reject) the assignment of a help desk call.
The system should provide the ability to automatically assign a priority and a target closure date to a help desk call, based on the category, service, or type of the call.
The system should provide the ability to automatically close a help desk call if the user does not respond to a request for more information after a specified amount of time.
The system should provide the ability to check for similar help desk calls.
The system should provide the ability to configure alerts for urgent RFCs.
The system should provide the ability to copy the details of a help desk call to a problem record.
The system should provide the ability to copy the details of a problem record to a RFC.
The system should provide the ability to create user profiles by copying an existing profile.
The system should provide the ability to define business rules to link the status of a help desk call with the status of a problem record.

The system should provide the ability to define parameters and rules for automatically escalating help desk calls based on the priority of the call, the time open, and the service type. The system shall support functional and hierarchical escalation.

The system should provide the ability to define parameters and rules for automatically escalating problem records based on the priority of the problem, the time open, and the service type. The system shall support functional and hierarchical escalation.
The system should provide the ability to display an item's branch tree graphically and allow operations from the tree.
The system should provide the ability to display the results of a report in various types of graphs and charts.
The system should provide the ability to flag a help desk call that requires an Incident Report.

The system should provide the ability to integrate with 3rd party auto-discovery, inventory, and audit tools such as Novell ZENworks for the initial load of CIs and for comparing CI baselines with the actual configurations.
The system should provide the ability to restrict which users are able to close a problem (e.g. only the Problem Manager user can close a problem).
The system should provide the ability to select multiple help desk calls and then carry out a specified operation on the selected calls.
The system should provide the ability to track the amount of time spent on resolving a problem.
The system should provide the ability to track the duration of service outage or severe service level degradation.
The system should provide the ability to track the forward schedule of changes.
The system should provide the ability to track the users affected by a help desk call.
The system should provide the ability to track the users affected by a problem.
The system should support personalisation of menus via creation of a favourite menu of the most-used transactions.
The web-based client of the system shall run on Microsoft Internet Explorer version 6.0 SP1 and higher.
Upon submitting a help desk call, the system shall provide the ability to send an automatic email notification to the user to confirm that a help desk call was successfully submitted.
